{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017eHhQfLm1p5huiJi8UMa4q","type":"tool_result","content":"total 64\ndrwxr-xr-x  4 501  staff 4096 Jul  2 08:04 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 11 501  staff 4096 Jul  2 08:04 ..\n-rw-r--r--  1 501  staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._CLAUDE.md\n-rw-r--r--  1 501  staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._GOAL.txt\n-rw-r--r--  1 501  staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._TASK.md\n-rwxr-xr-x  1 501  staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._inputs\n-rwxr-xr-x  1 501  staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._output\n-rwxr-xr-x  1 501  staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._run.sh\n-rw-r--r--  1 501  staff  521 Jul  2 08:04 CLAUDE.md\n-rw-r--r--  1 501  staff 1230 Jul  2 08:04 GOAL.txt\n-rw-r--r--  1 501  staff 2457 Jul  2 08:04 TASK.md\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 501  staff 4096 Jul  2 08:04 inputs\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 501  staff 4096 Jul  2 08:04 output\n-rw-r--r--  1 root root  4624 Jul  2 08:04 run.log\n-rwxr-xr-x  1 501  staff  318 Jul  2 08:04 run.sh\n---TASK---\n# TASK — Calculation note: passive reactor cavity cooling\n\nYou are an engineer. Produce a **calculation note** for a passive **Reactor Cavity Cooling\nSystem (RCCS)** — the system that removes a high-temperature reactor's decay heat after shutdown\nwith **no pumps**: a hot vessel wall transfers heat across an air-filled cavity to a bank of\nsteel riser ducts, and the air in those ducts warms, rises by buoyancy, and carries the heat up\na chimney by natural circulation.\n\nEverything you need is in **`inputs/`** — facility geometry, materials, operating conditions, and\nwhere each quantity is measured.\n\n## What we want\n\nFor the operating cases in `inputs/04_boundary_conditions_and_test_cases.md`, predict and report\n— with your reasoning and assumptions:\n\n- the natural-circulation air **mass flow rate**;\n- the air **temperature rise** across the riser ducts;\n- the **riser duct wall temperature** and the **heated-wall (mock-vessel) temperature**;\n- how the removed heat splits between **radiation and convection**;\n- for the accident (decay-heat) case: the **peak temperatures**, and whether the vessel **stays\n  below a safe limit** (does the temperature level off, or run away?);\n- how performance changes with the **outdoor ambient conditions** (air temperature, wind).\n\nState your confidence in each number and which assumption is the most uncertain.\n\nThe heated-wall and riser-wall temperatures must be **cross-checked by an independent,\nhigher-fidelity simulation that SOLVES for those temperatures** — do not prescribe the\ntemperatures you are trying to verify as boundary conditions. Drive the simulation with the heat\ninput (e.g. a heat-flux or heater-power boundary condition) and let it predict the wall\ntemperatures, including radiation. Conjugate heat transfer is welcome but not required; what\nmatters is that the temperatures are outputs, not inputs. Reconcile with your reduced model.\nPrefer prebuilt binaries or Docker; never compile a large code from source.\n\n## How to work\n\n- You choose the methods and tools. Build from physics and the given conditions.\n- Put the calculation note and all working files (scripts, models, intermediate results) in\n  **`output/`**.\n\n## Rules\n\n- Do **not** look up this facility's published test reports or any pre-made model of it. (They\n  exist online, and in `refs/` and `sources/` — all off-limits.) Predict the numbers yourself.\n- Cite the source of any empirical correlation you use.\n---INPUTS---\ntotal 52\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 501 staff 4096 Jul  2 08:04 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 4 501 staff 4096 Jul  2 08:04 ..\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._01_facility_geometry.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._02_materials_and_properties.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._03_instrumentation_map.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._04_boundary_conditions_and_test_cases.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._README.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff 6413 Jul  2 08:04 01_facility_geometry.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff 1875 Jul  2 08:04 02_materials_and_properties.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff 3996 Jul  2 08:04 03_instrumentation_map.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff 2860 Jul  2 08:04 04_boundary_conditions_and_test_cases.md\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  794 Jul  2 08:04 README.md\n---OUTPUT---\ntotal 8\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 501 staff 4096 Jul  2 08:04 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 4 501 staff 4096 Jul  2 08:04 ..","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"26147f87-2f88-4e84-a8c5-76251565da6d","uuid":"2615ed2a-1dab-41b1-8bbf-d41063975f48","timestamp":"2026-07-02T08:04:30.003Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"total 64\ndrwxr-xr-x  4 501  staff 4096 Jul  2 08:04 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 11 501  staff 4096 Jul  2 08:04 ..\n-rw-r--r--  1 501  staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._CLAUDE.md\n-rw-r--r--  1 501  staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._GOAL.txt\n-rw-r--r--  1 501  staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._TASK.md\n-rwxr-xr-x  1 501  staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._inputs\n-rwxr-xr-x  1 501  staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._output\n-rwxr-xr-x  1 501  staff  163 Jul  2 08:04 ._run.sh\n-rw-r--r--  1 501  staff  521 Jul  2 08:04 CLAUDE.md\n-rw-r--r--  1 501  staff 1230 Jul  2 08:04 GOAL.txt\n-rw-r--r--  1 501  staff 2457 Jul  2 08:04 TASK.md\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 501  staff 4096 Jul  2 08:04 inputs\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 501  staff 4096 Jul  2 08:04 output\n-rw-r--r--  1 root root  4624 Jul  2 08:04 run.log\n-rwxr-xr-x  1 501  staff  318 Jul  2 08:04 run.sh\n---TASK---\n# TASK — Calculation note: passive reactor cavity cooling\n\nYou are an engineer. Produce a **calculation note** for a passive **Reactor Cavity Cooling\nSystem (RCCS)** — the system that removes a high-temperature reactor's decay heat after shutdown\nwith **no pumps**: a hot vessel wall transfers heat across an air-filled cavity to a bank of\nsteel riser ducts, and the air in those ducts warms, rises by buoyancy, and carries the heat up\na chimney by natural circulation.\n\nEverything you need is in **`inputs/`** — facility geometry, materials, operating conditions, and\nwhere each quantity is measured.\n\n## What we want\n\nFor the operating cases in `inputs/04_boundary_conditions_and_test_cases.md`, predict and report\n— with your reasoning and assumptions:\n\n- the natural-circulation air **mass flow rate**;\n- the air **temperature rise** across the riser ducts;\n- the **riser duct wall temperature** and the **heated-wall (mock-vessel) temperature**;\n- how the removed heat splits between **radiation and convection**;\n- for the accident (decay-heat) case: the **peak temperatures**, and whether the vessel **stays\n  below a safe limit** (does the temperature level off, or run away?);\n- how performance changes with the **outdoor ambient conditions** (air temperature, wind).\n\nState your confidence in each number and which assumption is the most uncertain.\n\nThe heated-wall and riser-wall temperatures must be **cross-checked by an independent,\nhigher-fidelity simulation that SOLVES for those temperatures** — do not prescribe the\ntemperatures you are trying to verify as boundary conditions. Drive the simulation with the heat\ninput (e.g. a heat-flux or heater-power boundary condition) and let it predict the wall\ntemperatures, including radiation. Conjugate heat transfer is welcome but not required; what\nmatters is that the temperatures are outputs, not inputs. Reconcile with your reduced model.\nPrefer prebuilt binaries or Docker; never compile a large code from source.\n\n## How to work\n\n- You choose the methods and tools. Build from physics and the given conditions.\n- Put the calculation note and all working files (scripts, models, intermediate results) in\n  **`output/`**.\n\n## Rules\n\n- Do **not** look up this facility's published test reports or any pre-made model of it. (They\n  exist online, and in `refs/` and `sources/` — all off-limits.) Predict the numbers yourself.\n- Cite the source of any empirical correlation you use.\n---INPUTS---\ntotal 52\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 501 staff 4096 Jul  2 08:04 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 4 501 staff 4096 Jul  2 08:04 ..\n-rw-r--r-- 1 501 staff  163 Jul  2 08:0