{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01SAPMrXU5AWM5BrWkL8eHtt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All deliverables are complete and verified. The goal is met.\n\n## Summary\n\nI completed the RCCS calculation note in `output/calculation_note.md`, built entirely from the inputs and first-principles physics (no facility data consulted — stated in the provenance line).\n\n**Two independent models, reconciled:**\n\n1. **Reduced 0-D/1-D loop model** (`model.py`, `cases.py`) — couples the buoyant-draft/loss momentum balance, energy balance, a cavity radiation + enclosed-natural-convection network, internal Gnielinski convection, and a circumferential perimeter-fin solve for the hot-face temperature.\n\n2. **Independent higher-fidelity CFD** (`cfd/rccs2d`, OpenFOAM `buoyantSimpleFoam` + fvDOM radiation, in Docker) — a 2-D buoyant cavity slice where the **heat flux is prescribed and the wall temperatures are solved outputs**, with radiation included. Getting the stiff fixed-flux+radiation coupling to converge required a flux-ramping strategy, which succeeded.\n\n**Headline results (Case 1, Q_air = 56 kW):**\n\n| Quantity | Reduced | CFD cross-check |\n|---|---|---|\n| Mass flow | 0.57 kg/s = 34 kg/min | — |\n| Air ΔT | 97 °C | — |\n| Heated-wall (plate) T | 372 °C | 333 °C |\n| Riser wall T (z=3.5 m) | 131 °C mean / 181 °C front | 122–124 °C mean |\n| Radiation / convection | 91 % / 9 % | 89 % / 11 % |\n| Accident peak | ≈372 °C — **levels off, < 550 °C** | — |\n\nAll seven required items are addressed with assumptions and confidence levels: mass flow, air ΔT, riser & plate wall temperatures, the radiation/convection split (~90 % radiation, independently confirmed), the accident case (quasi-steady, τ≈2 h ≪ 85 h transient → levels off, no runaway, stays below the ~550 °C limit), weather sensitivity (colder/denser outdoor air → more draft; wind as a worst-case adverse dynamic head), and the CFD cross-check that solves for the temperatures. The parasitic-loss estimate (`parasitic.py`) independently reproduces the 82 kWe → 56 kW air-side split. Figures and `results.json` accompany the note; `README.md` documents reproduction.\n\nThe most uncertain single input is the air-side heat (Q_air ≈ 56 kW, ±15%, dominated by the uninsulated outlet-plenum loss), followed by the assumed riser emissivity (0.80) and the cavity view factor — the latter two cross-checked by the CFD."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":845,"cache_read_input_tokens":235868,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":845},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"26147f87-2f88-4e84-a8c5-76251565da6d","uuid":"f7c065cf-3119-426a-939f-dd5734ad06e9","request_id":"req_011CccxZk6EW6jP55hNTcsF6"}
